{
  "html": "<div id=\"BUV\" class=\"uplift front\">\n    <div id=\"course-front-body\" class=\"responsive-padding\" style=\"color: #2d3b45; background: none; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px;\">\n        <article id=\"course-lesson-intro-text\" style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\n            <h3 class=\"heavy\" style=\"margin: 0; font-size: 2.7em;\">Gameplay Applications</h3>\n            <p>This module challenges you to take what you have learned about mechanics and metrics and apply it to the development and iteration of an analogue game. Emphasis is placed on originality, polish and balance. To achieve this, it is expected that you will go through an iterative process of design, test and redesign of your game at least once every ten days (8 tests per semester), recording feedback on your game and then immediately making changes to it.</p>\n        </article>\n        <section class=\"grid-row\">\n            <article class=\"col-lg-4 buv-responsive-video-100\" style=\"padding-left: 12px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 20px;\"><iframe class=\"lti-embed bgcover\" style=\"display: inline-block; border: none; background: #f7f7f7;\" title=\"Module intro video\" src=\"\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"webkitallowfullscreen\" mozallowfullscreen=\"mozallowfullscreen\" allow=\"geolocation *; microphone *; camera *; midi *; encrypted-media *; autoplay *; clipboard-write *; display-capture *\" data-studio-resizable=\"true\" data-studio-tray-enabled=\"true\" data-studio-convertible-to-link=\"true\" data-mce-fragment=\"1\"></iframe></article>\n            <article class=\"col-lg-8\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; padding-left: 12px;\">\n                <h3><strong>Learning Objectives:</strong></h3>\n                <p><span style=\"color: #ba372a; font-size: 14pt;\">+ &nbsp;</span>Analyse researched information in order to plan a project that fulfils the identified needs of a modern game.</p>\n                <p><span style=\"color: #ba372a; font-size: 14pt;\">+ &nbsp;</span>Evaluate the appropriateness of choices and varied approaches to solving problems that occur during the preparation and presentation of gameplay mechanics.</p>\n                <p><span style=\"color: #ba372a; font-size: 14pt;\">+ &nbsp;</span>Determine game characteristics and mechanics in order to select appropriate tools and methods required to support the design and development of a rapid prototype game.</p>\n                <p><span style=\"color: #ba372a; font-size: 14pt;\">+ &nbsp;</span>Plan and create an analogue game that utilises the correct documentation</p>\n                <p><span style=\"color: #ba372a; font-size: 14pt;\">+ &nbsp;</span>Review the project creation process evaluating the effectiveness of your role during the project.</p>\n            </article>\n        </section>\n    </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"grid-row responsive-padding\" style=\"padding-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; margin-bottom: -50px;\">\n    <h3 style=\"padding-left: 12px;\"><strong>Module Content:</strong></h3>\n</div>",
